# MTG card images + unified treatment

Where possible, use **Scryfall card images** for pickers, queues, selection, and swap UIs — not card-name lists.

## Shared kit (`packages/web/src/cards/`)

- `CardFace` — image + foil gem + qty badge (same radius via `--db-card-radius`)
- `CardSizePicker` / `useCardSize` — S/M/L, key `rayenzHubPickerCardSize`
- `CardPicker` / `installHubCardPickerBridge` — React replacement for `HubCardPicker`

## Prefer

- `CardFace`, `CardTile`, swap `MiniCard`, or `CardPicker` image grids via `cardImageUrl` / Scryfall URLs
- Names as `alt` text, image-load fallbacks, or tooltips only

## Avoid

- Name-only `<select>` / text lists for choosing cards when an image affordance can work
- Parallel card chrome (different radius, foil badge, or size control) outside the shared kit
- Loading vanilla `shared/card-picker.js` alongside the React bridge

## Exception

Explicit list/name layouts (or a future list view mode) may use card names as the primary display. Filters that narrow an image grid by name are fine as auxiliary controls.
